    </ac:structured-macro>
</h2>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Overview</h2>
<p>
    This page documents the Admin Service Type intake flow in R4C (Return for Credit): how an Agent logs in, creates
    an Admin case, adds and validates line items, and moves the case through to completion, including the Case Edit
    flows for both Internally-originated and ILM-originated cases.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Give Developers and QA a single, accurate reference for the Admin intake case
    lifecycle, including case creation, request header and collection details, line item search/upload and credit
    price validation, case view/edit behavior, and the checks (SAP blocks, CPN indicator) that govern it.
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.3. ">Pre-Requisites </h2>
<p>
    To login as an agent, we should have Sandbox access for the required test environment. We have two types of Agents
    L1 &amp; L2. L1 Agent can login to the Sandbox URL and create a Return Request for Stock Rotation. L2 Agent can view
    the cases assigned to them and can change the case owner.
</p>
<p>
    <strong> Sandbox (IAO QA) Link: </strong> <a href="https://isvc--isvciaoqa.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/"> <strong>
            https://isvc--isvciaoqa.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/ </strong> </a>
</p>
<p>
    Access related issues, Contact: @Indus ISVC GRL R4C
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.4. ">Login to CRM R4C System</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Enter the sandbox URL in the browser and login as an L1 Agent with your user credentials.</li>
    <li>After we login to the system, we will be able to see the app “Return for Credit ”, and “ Home” Tab .</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="f41ef451-2ae1-faeb-5f65-8e3c38bb0ba8" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>If ‘ Return for Credit ’ a pp is not displayed directly after login , then click on App launcher ( nine dots
            ) , search for “ R eturn for credit” and select first option.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.5. ">Case creation</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Select ‘Contact’ from the ‘Navigation items/ Menu’ dropdown</li>
    <li>Select a contact from the list view of contacts to open corresponding contact record.</li>
    <li>In the contact detail page, we can see “Create R4C Case” link &amp; “New R4C Case” Button, click on one of them.
    </li>
    <li>When Clicking on a contact hyperlink the page opens in a new tab and if clicked on the button then the “Step1
        Dialog box for Service type selection “is opened. “ Tech nical” is selected by default, Agent needs to select
        Admin for Admin Service Type.</li>
    <li>The New R4C Case subtab will be opened after clicking on the Create button. Fill in the Request header details
        &amp; Collection Details.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">SAP Blocks scenarios</h2>
<p>
    Before a Sold To, Payer or Ship To can be used on a case, R4C checks Export Compliance, Order, Billing and
    Delivery blocks at CMF and Sales Area level. Block values, hard-stop behavior, and how Case creation differs
    from Case edit are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Block Scenarios" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for the block rules.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Admin Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Case creation: any Sold To CMF, Sales Area or Ship To CMF/Sales Area with a hard block is excluded from its
        respective selection dropdown; a Payer-level block surfaces as an error toast on Sold To selection.</li>
    <li>Case edit: a hard block present at Sold To CMF, Sales Area, Payer or Ship To level blocks the Edit action
        with an error toast.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Request Header Details </h2>
<ul>
    <li>User should fill in all the mandatory fields which are marked with the red colour asterisk symbol (*) and until
        all mandatory fields are entered, next button should be disabled.</li>
    <li>Contact Name &amp; Account Name will be auto populated as Hyperlinks. The selected Service Type is shown as the
        text field.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Sold To/Ship To CMF resolution, wildcard search, and address auto-population rules are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Address &amp; Contact Management" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Admin Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong> Remedy: </strong> For Service type “ Admin ” the possible remedy value is ‘Credit ’. It will be auto
        populated in the dropdown.</li>
    <li><strong> Return Reason : </strong> These values are determined based on the selected ‘Service Type’ and
        ‘Remedy ’ . Values are fetched from the ‘Customer Return Reasons’ object and displayed in dropdown for
        agent to choose from.</li>
    <li><strong> CIRS Number: </strong> This is the input text where agent need to enter a random number by
        using the format ( <strong> CIxxxx-xxxx ) </strong> where x is any number .</li>
    <li><strong> Description </strong> : Agent can provide the issue details in case notes field.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.8. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Collection Details</h2>
<p>
    Return to Customer/Collection Address &amp; Contact resolution, Freight Type (IMF/CRF), Incoterm Determination,
    Return Location, Origin Bond, the LAR Country rule, Address/Contact Add-Edit-Delete, the Google Address
    Autocomplete API, the China Contact Consent Confirmation, and the Embargo Check (GTS Screening) are documented
    once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Address &amp; Contact Management" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<ul>
    <li>After selecting all mandatory fields ‘Next’ button will be enabled</li>
    <li>By clicking on the ‘Next’ button agent can proceed further.</li>
    <li>By clicking on the ‘Cancel’ button user can stop the case creation process and navigate back to the contact
        page.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.9. ">Search/Upload Line Item </h2>
<ul>
    <li>Search By option is further divided into:
        <ul>
            <li>Purchase/Sales Order search using:
                <ul>
                    <li>PO Number (Purchase Order Number)</li>
                    <li>SO Number (Sales Order Number)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Product Search using:
                <ul>
                    <li>MM (Material master identification)</li>
                    <li>CPN (Customer Part Number)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Upload: User can able to download MMCPN/ULT Templates &amp; can able to upload here using</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Bulk Upload option.
</p>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.1. ">Purchase / Sales Order Search</h3>
<ul>
    <li>By using the above interface, agent can search for line items using single or multiple comma separated ‘PO
        Numbers’ or ‘SO Numbers ’.</li>
    <li>On click of Search button, on the backend date range is automatically set for 3 month , search process is
        halted, and agent is notified by warning toast message .</li>
    <li>Agent can reset the search data by clicking on the Reset bu tton .</li>
    <li>After agent enters the PO or SO number(s), that search data is sent to ‘ ECA API’ on click of the “Search”
        button to get line items details from ‘ ECA API ’.</li>
    <li>If no response is obtained, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message ‘Records not
        found/Please check your PO number which you entered ’.</li>
    <li>The line-item data obtained as response from API is again validated in database using Item Type ‘FERT’ check .
        If Item type of line items is not ‘FERT’ then line items are disabled.</li>
    <li>Agent can select the line items from valid line-item data, at which point ‘Next’ and ‘Save for Later’ buttons
        would be enabled for agent to proceed to next step ‘ Credit Price Validation ’.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="abb05a0c-8191-8dfa-5f96-61af4b7860b9" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>On click of ‘Next’ button, Agent needs to select <strong> only one line item </strong> to proceed to further
            steps , else it is a hard stop to proceed further.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Product Search</h3>
<p>
    The MM/CPN radio search mechanics, the Multiple CPN Scenario, and the PO History/Validate PO button flow are
    documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Admin Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Line-item data is validated using Item Type <strong>‘FERT’</strong> only. If Item type of a line item is
        not ‘FERT’, that line item is disabled.</li>
    <li>PO History validation is called via the <strong>ECA API</strong> (renamed from HANA API, see Revisions
        v1.2, 07/07/2026).</li>
    <li>The initial PO History date range is Current date – 3 months.</li>
    <li>On click of ‘Next’ button, Agent needs to select <strong>only one line item</strong> to proceed to further
        steps, else it is a hard stop to proceed further.</li>
    <li>Agent can select the line items from valid line-item data, at which point ‘Validate PO(s)’, ‘Next’ and
        ‘Save for Later’ buttons would be enabled for agent to proceed to next step ‘Warranty Entitlement Check
        Validation’.</li>
    <li>Agent can reset the line-item data by clicking on the “Reset” button.</li>
    <li>Agent can see the “Delete Line item” column in Line item table.
        <ul>
            <li>In Case creation, on click of ‘Delete’ button the Line item will be removed from the Line item list.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    In Case Edit, on click of ‘Delete’ button the Line item will get unselected from the Line item list &amp; that Line
    item will not proceed to next steps.
</p>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.3. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Bulk Upload</h3>
<p>
    The CSV template/drag-drop/Validate mechanics and the PO History/Validate PO button flow are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Admin Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Template sample:</li>
    <li>Here for each line-item data entered, MM number or CPN number should be mandatorily entered along with Return
        quantity. All other fields are optional, and data entered will be mapped to the particular line-item column
        in respective stages.</li>
    <li>If agent wants to specify ‘Return Package Conditions’, the acceptable values are ‘Outer Box Opened – Product
        Unsealed’ and ‘Box closed – Factory sealed’. All other values would be invalid.</li>
    <li>PO History validation is called via the ECA API (see the note in Product Search above about this naming),
        with an initial date range of Current date – 3 months, and is bypassed for line items coming from PO Search
        and Validate PO.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="b5bc5f3e-d7bd-d67e-688d-3fa202a610c8" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>After clicking <strong> Next </strong> after <strong> PO History </strong> , <strong> Disti Product status
                check validation </strong> will happen here and following Product status check validation will be done
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    The Disti Channel Product Status check mechanism and its IAO-flag/field split are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    . Admin Intake documents the following code list:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are allowing for Agent Case creation: 35 (Active), 45 (End
        of Life), 75 (Obsolete), 65 (Retired), 25 (QR Hold), 55 (No order after LOED).</li>
    <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are not allowing for Agent Case creation: 15 (Pre Active),
        05 (Concept).</li>
    <li>When we try to create case with product status 15 and 05 it will be a Hardstop and will show a error message
        saying “Current status is 15 (Pre Active)” and for 05 “current status is 05 (Concept)”.</li>
    <li>If the Product status is not valid or empty (null), an error message is displayed: “No valid product status
        were found”.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="2db09609-f898-b40a-5e26-8c65d75db3be" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>On click of ‘Next’ button, Agent needs to select <strong> only one line item </strong> to proceed to
            further steps, else it is a hard stop to proceed further.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
    <li>If the agent is in Credit price step and wants to change the line item, he should deselect the current line
        item in the step 2 and go back to search page to add new line item.</li>
    <li>If agent adds the new line item, then on click of next button if the agent has not deselected the previous
        line item which is in step 2, he will be notified to clear the line items in step 2 first to proceed with
        adding new one.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.10. ">Credit Price Validation</h2>
<ul>
    <li>In “Credit Price Validation” section a gent can see “Get Credit Price” button enabled for all selected line
        items .</li>
    <li>Enter the Return Quantity for each line item as it is mandatory field. Return Po &amp; Debit Reference number
        are optional fields.</li>
    <li>Once agent clicks on ‘Get Credit Price’ button :</li>
    <li>T he Credit Price of Line item will be determined by SalesOrderLineNetPriceAmt attribute value of ECA API .</li>
    <li>‘Net credit Value’ of each valid line item is calculated as ‘Return Quantity’ * ‘Credit Price’ and is displayed
        in ‘Net credit value’ column.</li>
    <li>Agent also has the option to select the ‘Box Condition’ of each line item.</li>
    <li>After successfully obtaining credit price, ‘Save &amp; View Summary’ button is enabled so agent can move to view
        page.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="d7e90fd6-ab3c-7dda-f446-7f1d33c3b417" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>If Return Reason is <strong> ‘Wrong Product’ </strong> or <strong> ‘Duplicate Order ’ </strong> , where agent
            needs to set the credit price of the line item to ‘0’ to create a successful case .</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
    <li>In Admin Intake we have two scenarios where agent needs to set the credit price of all line items to ‘0’ to
        create a successful case if he selects those two particular return reasons .</li>
    <li>Those scenarios occur when the selected Remedy is <strong> ‘Credit’ </strong> and Return Reason selected is
        either <strong> ‘Wrong Product’ </strong> or <strong> ‘Duplicate Order ’. </strong></li>
    <li>Here credit price is fetched from ECA system.</li>
    <li>If price of all line items is <strong> not set </strong> to ‘0’, then on click of “Save and View summary Button”
        agent is shown an error toast message to set the credit price as zero as shown below.</li>
    <li>Here the agent needs to change the price to zero and fill in the Reason for Price change input column.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="3c14fdd1-fa3a-4630-a6ee-e0546c79f6e3" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>If Return Reason is <strong> ‘Lost Shipment ',' Wrong destination ',' Sample 'and ' Overship ' </strong>
                where Price can change it to zero ( <strong> 0) </strong> .</li>
            <li>if not Zero <strong> (0), Price </strong> should be the same which is fetched from <strong> PO price
                </strong> to create a successful case .</li>
            <li>Once credit price validation is done for particular line item(s), credit price validation button will be
                disabled and obtained credit price value will be considered valid for current day. So, if agent edits
                case or comes back to ‘Credit Validation’ stage on same day, no API callout is required as previously
                fetched value will be auto populated.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="9b5cc98c-7521-0ade-e093-3526f4e7fc69" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>For CPN Support Customer, If the CPN is not available for line items then MMCPN API will call on click of
            ‘Save for Later’ &amp; ‘Save &amp; View Summary’ buttons &amp; populate the CPN at line item level otherwise
            the line items which are not having CPN are disabled with error message &amp; User not able to create Case
            with non-CPN line items.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.11. ">View Summary Page</h2>
<ul>
    <li>On clicking the button, agent is navigated to ‘Save &amp; View summary’/’Ready to Submit’ page .</li>
    <li>Here agent can see all the case details briefly and confirm if everything is correct before he can submit the
        case.</li>
    <li>Agent can see “Edit ”, “ C ancel” and “Submit” buttons .</li>
    <li>In case of any soft blocks (SAP blocks or other), ‘Submit’ button will be disabled and agent would be notified
        by a toast message about the presence of soft blocks.</li>
    <li>Then agent can edit the case again or continue and submit the case if no soft blocks are present .</li>
    <li>On click of Submit button , the case is submitted with case status as ‘Pending Approval’ and agent is redirected
        to the ‘Case Detail Page ’.</li>
    <li>If agent click s on cancel then the case is saved with “ O pen, U nsubmitted” status and agent is redirected to
        the related ‘ Case Detail Page ’ .</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="7f9a46c7-851f-f1d3-1839-d403f2a75308" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Email Approval Scenario</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>For Admin Intake every case must first be approved by external approver for getting ‘RMA Authorized ’ .
            </li>
            <li>O n load of ‘View Summary page ’, email of external approver is fetched from ‘ ILM Approval Matrix’ by
                sending sold to CMF, service type, approver source, Location Geography along with valid ‘F rom ’ and ‘
                To ’ dates .</li>
            <li>On click of ‘Submit’ button, case status is set to ‘Pending Approval’ and email is sent to approver for
                approval.</li>
            <li>If no approver record is found, agent is notified by error toast message.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.12. ">Case View </h2>
<ul>
    <li>The Case c an be viewed either by going to contact and then click on related tab and can also be viewed by
        Searching with Case Number and the Case view is as follows :</li>
    <li>Here in the case view page, we can see the details of case in Details tab, in R4C Case Header tab we can see the
        details of the Header object as shown below.</li>
    <li>We have a tab called R4C Shipment tab, where shipment status can be tracked of each line item.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.13. ">Case Edit Flow ( Case Origin – Internal) </h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong> For RMA Authorized Cases </strong> , Only RTC Address and RTC Contacts c an be edited, and we can’t
        edit anything else.</li>
    <li><strong> For Open, Unsubmitted cases, </strong> we check SAP Blocks on Load when the Edit R4C button is clicked,
        and if any hard blocks existing or if any inactive records are part of case, then it’s a hard stop and Agents
        can ’ t edit the case else if no blocks and no inactive CMFs Agent can edit all the Collection details as well
        as Line Items</li>
    <li>The Default landing page for the line items is Search/Upload Line Items Page , line items can be deleted by
        using dropdown or unselect the line items, in the data base, the line items status get s set to D eleted .
        <ul>
            <li>Cancel Line Items:</li>
            <li>In Edit Case tab, we have an additional column ‘Line items status’ where agent can select to delete line
                items.</li>
            <li>If agent selects ‘ delete ’ , then he will be shown a prompt to confirm if he really wants to delete the
                line item.</li>
            <li>Agent can also unselect the line items which will have same functionality as selecting ‘ Delete ’
                status.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong> For Pending Approval Cases , </strong> Only RTC Address, RTC Contact field s can be edited,
        additionally If Freight Type is IMF, Collection Date can also be edited .</li>
    <li><strong> RTC/Collection, Date Edit scenarios </strong> : After clicking on Edit button, agent can be able to
        edit RTC/Collection address, Date fields for the RMA Authorised cases.</li>
    <li>RTCAddressChange , CollectionAddressChange , CollectionDateChange indicators will get updated in ECC at header
        level.</li>
    <li>ECC will update the records once case submitted in SF.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.14. ">ILM Case Edit flow ( Case Origin – ILM) </h2>
<ul>
    <li>The user can edit the ILM case and able to set the price only to zero . Cannot be changed to other value.</li>
    <li>The following scenarios should be considered while edit the case
        <ul>
            <li>Case Status should be
                <ul>
                    <li>RMA Authorized</li>
                    <li>Pending Carrier Booking</li>
                    <li>Pickup Requested</li>
                    <li>Awaiting Scheduled Pickup</li>
                    <li>In Process</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Line Item should be</li>
    <li>Pending Carrier Booking</li>
    <li>Pickup requested</li>
    <li>Awaiting Scheduled Pickup</li>
    <li>In Transit</li>
    <li>Delivered</li>
    <li>Exception</li>
    <li>Discrepant</li>
    <li>Return Reason should be</li>
    <li>Wrong Product</li>
    <li>Lost Shipment</li>
    <li><strong> Note s in Edit Scenario : </strong>
        <ul>
            <li>For Admin Intake, when age n t edits the case , he cannot increase the Return Quantity of any line item.
                He is only allowed to decrease it. In case agent increases Return Quantity of any line item , ‘Save’
                button is disabled and agent notified by error message .</li>
            <li>If case is being edited and the earlier and line items are gone beyond Credit Price Validation step and
                earlier detected credit price is on same day, then credit price validation API call is bypassed for
                existing line items.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
